The paper discusses knowledge representation in AI, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes a generative model for knowledge graph embedding, which involves learning low-dimensional representations of symbolic entities and relations. This falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of semantic expression in knowledge representation, which is relevant to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves experiments to justify the effectiveness of the proposed model, which falls under the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Databases (cs.DB).
